==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: boscage
<hw>bos"cage</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>boscage</ets> grove, F. <ets>bocage</ets>, fr. LL.
<ets>boscus</ets>, <ets>buscus</ets>, thicket, wood. See 1st
<er>Bush</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A growth of trees or shrubs;
underwood; a thicket; thick foliage; a wooded landscape.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(O. Eng. Law)</fld> <def>Food or sustenance for
cattle, obtained from bushes and trees; also, a tax on wood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

